|CKBStreet Samurai Combat Monitor|000

|CKBUsing the monitor|000
|CK0The standard monitor command can print HP, SP, and Cortex combat state when
your HP or SP changes. Use monitor on for the compact display, monitor bar for
resource bars, or monitor off to disable automatic updates. The hp and .
commands always request a current snapshot manually.|000

|CK0The Cortex line begins with the cortexmesh shell prompt. It shows current
and maximum Edge, current and maximum Heat, the live thermal state, and compact
process indicators. PAUSED means the contract is inactive. UNMANAGED means the
Cortex OS is missing. LOCKOUT means Heat-producing firmware cannot run until
the system cools.|000

|CKBProcess indicators|000
|CK0A green {X} means a process is online, active, or ready. A red {X} means it
is offline, unavailable, or spent. The indicators are:|000

|CK0OC - Overclock is currently running.
OD - Overdrive readiness is available for the current engagement.
AW - Armor Weave shielding is active.
SM - Your Smart Smoke is active in the current room.
TB - Trauma Buffer is delaying incoming damage.
MW - Monowire is deployed; this does not show whether a breach is armed.
JF - Your Jammer Field is active in the current room.
PS - Predictive Sight is active.
GS - A Ghoststep avoidance frame is armed.
ZS - Zero Signal is active.
TS - Threat Scan has at least one active target lock.|000

|CK0OD represents readiness rather than a persistent buff. It turns red after
Overdrive has handled the opening Heat burst for the current engagement. TS
does not identify which target is locked; Threat Scan output and combat
messages provide that context. Room-local indicators turn red after you leave
the room containing their effect.|000

|CKBRefresh timing|000
|CK0The line refreshes when the normal HP or SP monitor redraws. Heat may cool,
a lock may expire, or an effect may end between redraws. Use hp or . for an
immediate reading, samstatus for a detailed local state query, and dashboard
for implant condition and alerts.|000

|CK0Screen-reader mode replaces the compact abbreviations with complete process
names and status sentences. Turning the automatic monitor off does not disable
Street Samurai resources or firmware; it only stops automatic display updates.|000
